From e97cb86637f311e86459cc34501a1098996a60dd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hari Naraayana Desikan Kannan <hnaraaya@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Dec 2025 15:30:45 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Lower verbosity for
 high-frequency management logs

High-frequency management frames (Probe Request/Response, Action, Beacon)
and EHT/MLD capability reporting can generate thousands of log lines per
second at common debug levels in dense environments, drowning out
actionable messages.

Move these logs to MSG_EXCESSIVE (visible only with -dddd):

- nl80211: send_mlme, CMD_FRAME, RX frame, MLME event, and frequency
  parameters for Probe/Action/Beacon subtypes
- hostapd: MLD per-STA profiles, EML/MLD capabilities, 6 GHz channel
  list, TPE, and HE MU EDCA for Probe/Action/Beacon frames
- Beacon updates: Use MSG_EXCESSIVE for routine beacon sets; keep
  initial beacon at MSG_DEBUG; escalate failures to MSG_ERROR
- Suppress "Unknown event" log for EVENT_UNPROT_BEACON

Signed-off-by: Hari Naraayana Desikan Kannan <hnaraaya@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
